Files:
oss.c
worker.c
Makefile

Compilation:
make

Execution example:
./oss -n 1 -s 1 -t 1 -f logfile.txt

Description:
oss launches worker processes and maintains a simulated system clock
in shared memory. Workers only run when oss sends them a message
via a message queue. Workers check the shared clock and determine
when they should terminate based on their assigned runtime.

Output:
oss writes its output to both the screen and the logfile specified
with -f. Worker output appears only on the screen.